text: Nicholasville is an unincorporated community in Walton County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== A variant name was "Nickelville". According to tradition, the community was first called "Nickelville" because whiskey drinks were sold at the local country store for just one nickel. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Walton County, Georgia
title: Nicholasville, Georgia
